<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-258-312  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 258 312.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computer Reseller News  March 19 1990 n359 p41(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>A closer look at CeBIT: Hannover fair features 'anchor' firms,multiple exhibit halls. (Hannover Fair CeBIT in Hannover, WestGermany)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Hubbard, Holly.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Hannover Fair CeBIT 1990 will take place during the week of March26, 1990.andP;  The focus of the world's largest trade show involvingthe electronics, computer and communications industries will beupon the impending unification of the European market in 1992.andO;Over 4,000 companies will exhibit their products and systems atthe current show, which will be visited by more than 73,000 agentsand distributors from around the world, as well as by half amillion visitors.andP;  This year, the show will be divided intodifferent venues, with a special exhibit hall reserved forproducts designed for such vertical markets as banking andfinancial services, a hall reserved for networking systemshardware and software and a special forum dealing with jointventure projects between US companies and international vendors.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     CeBITComputer IndustryCommunications IndustrySingle European MarketInternational TradeTrade Shows.andO;Feature:   illustrationphotograph.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>